definition: name/noun (part of speech)/place (e.g. among winners)/famous/classifier for people
will/shall/to use/to take/to checkmate/just a short while ago/(introduces object of main verb, used in the same way as 把[ba3])

sentences.english: Men's pair oars were still the show place for the world-renownedrowers.
sentences.chinese: 男子雙人單槳仍然是名將的表演。

sentences.english: Police have charged a man with murder as a hate crime in her death.
sentences.chinese: 警方抓捕了一名男子，並以仇殺罪名將其歸案。

sentences.english: The winner will be consigned with the contract of entire design process.
sentences.chinese: 優勝方案的第一名將獲得本項目的全程設計委託合同。

sentences.english: Many of today's touring pros play with customized racquets .
sentences.chinese: 很多當今的網壇名將都自己定製自己的網球拍。

sentences.english: Still less while walloping the rest of the world's best in the pool?
sentences.chinese: 但要對抗其他世界泳池名將難道還是少了點嗎？

sentences.english: Typically, these names will manifest as a garbled sequence of characters.
sentences.chinese: 通常，這些文件名將顯示爲一個混亂的字符序列。

sentences.english: Server aliases will be compared with multidrop addresses by IP address.
sentences.chinese: 服務器假名將通過IP地址與多分支地址比較。

sentences.english: The idea pleased Zhang Yining, a table tennis player who is a household name in China.
sentences.chinese: 中國家喻戶曉的桌球名將張怡寧很欣賞這個構想。

sentences.english: I've had 12 students work on this for their graduate work.
sentences.chinese: 我和12名將其作爲畢業作品的同學一起爲此工作。

sentences.english: Ljubicic's ATP ranking will rise from 26 to 13 after this victory.
sentences.chinese: 這次獲勝，柳比西奇的ATP排名將從26升至13。

sentences.english: This 24-year-old tennis player was born in Slovakia.
sentences.chinese: 這位24歲的網球名將生在斯洛伐克。

sentences.english: You can map a message parameter to a correlation property using a property alias.
sentences.chinese: 可以使用屬性別名將消息參數映射到相關屬性。
